osed human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection, among persons aged ≥13 years in the United States during 1981-2008. From 1981 to 1995, the estimated annual num¬ber of deaths among persons with AIDS increased from 451 to 50,628. These increases were followed by declines of 45% in AIDS diagnoses from 1993 to 1998 and 63% in deaths from 1995 to 1998. AIDS diagnoses and deaths remained fairly stable at an average of 38,279 AIDS diagnoses and 17,489 deaths per year during 1999-2008. As a result, the estimated number of persons aged ≥13 years living with AIDS more than doubled from 1996 (219,318) to 2008 (479,161).","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":481,"renderedHeight":255,"naturalWidth":481,"naturalHeight":255,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 823 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":21509},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":1087},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_excel.gif","alt":"Microsoft Excel file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":